 in organizations leadership in diverse organizations entrepreneurial design for extreme affordability environmental science for managers and policy makers environmental science for managers and policy makers advanced homeland security operations strategy and implementation social enterprise strategic management of nonprofits social entrepreneurship strategic thinking in action in business and beyond entrepreneurship from the perspective of women all courses other eligible learning opportunities in addition to pre approved pmp courses you may take advantage of independant study options and courses across the university and petition for them to count toward a pmp certificate past examples include iper 310 environmental forum seminar pubpol 202b law and economics pubpol 207 political philosophy and ethics econ 250a natural resource and energy economics econ 122 economic development of latin america urban studies 131 social innovation & the social entrepreneur urban studies 132 concepts and analytic skills for the social sector urban studies 133 social entrepreneurship collaboratory admissions faculty & research alumni recruiters & companies giving executive education news about the gsb copyright 2009 stanford graduate school of business site help terms of use & policies stanford university
